wwpLeosPbtMIB.name: wwpLeosPbtMIB

revisions.description: This MIB module defines the managed objects for the PBT (Provider Backbone Transport) feature for LEOS based WWP products.

wwpLeosPbtMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosPbtMIB.description: Added objects wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitDestBridgeIndex, wwpLeosPbtTunnelSwitchOverHoldTime, WwpLeosTcePbtServiceEntry wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapEntry, wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupEntry, wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlEntry, wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlEntry, wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformEntry. Added Notifications wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelActivateNotification, wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelDeactivateNotification, wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelReversionNotification.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeMac.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeMac
wwpLeosPbtBridgeMac.description: This represents the provider mac address to be used as source mac during PBT encapsulation. If this object is not set then it will return default mac derived from chassis mac.

wwpLeosPbtServiceTagEType.name: wwpLeosPbtServiceTagEType
wwpLeosPbtServiceTagEType.description: This represents the etype value to be used in I-Tag (Service tag) section of PBT encapsulation. The I-tag ether type cannot be modified in native mode PBT

wwpLeosPbtTunnelTagEtype.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelTagEtype
wwpLeosPbtTunnelTagEtype.description: This represents the etype value to be used in B-Tag section of PBT encapsulation. Valid values are 8100, 9100 & 88a8

wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionState.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionState
wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionState.description: Setting this object will enable or disable automatic tunnel reversion from backup to primary if primary comes back up. Device will wait for wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionHoldTime before switching that data traffic back to primary automatically.

wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionHoldTime.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionHoldTime
wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionHoldTime.description: This object represents the hold time before data traffic on the backup tunnel will automatically revert to the primary tunnel.

wwpLeosPbtTransitTunnelEtypeRemark.name: wwpLeosPbtTransitTunnelEtypeRemark
wwpLeosPbtTransitTunnelEtypeRemark.description: Setting this object will enable or disable remarking of the EtherType field in the B-Tag (tunnel) portion of PBT frames that are transiting through the device without PBT encapsulation, nor decapsulation. While enabled, applicable PBT transit frames egressing a PBT enhanced port will have their B-Tag EtherType marked with the value configured as the wwpLeosPbtTunnelTagEtype.

wwpLeosPbtAdminMode.name: wwpLeosPbtAdminMode
wwpLeosPbtAdminMode.description: This object represents PBT Admin mode. Some platforms support either non-native or native mode.

wwpLeosPbtOperMode.name: wwpLeosPbtOperMode
wwpLeosPbtOperMode.description: This object represents PBT Oper mode. Some platforms support either non-native or native mode.

wwpLeosPbtServiceVlanTpid.name: wwpLeosPbtServiceVlanTpid
wwpLeosPbtServiceVlanTpid.description: When operating in native mode, this is the value of the service vlan TPID that will be used if retain-stag is set to TRUE. This is configurable only in native mode PBT. In non-native mode, this value defaults to the 0x8100 and cannot be changed. Valid values are 8100, 9100 and 88a8

wwpLeosPbtTunnelSwitchOverHoldTime.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelSwitchOverHoldTime
wwpLeosPbtTunnelSwitchOverHoldTime.description: This object represents the hold time before data traffic on backup tunnel will automatically switchover to primary tunnel.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapTable.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapTable
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the host names to mac mapping table. To create entry in this table use SNMP multiple set operation. - wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapBridgeName must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus must be specified.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapEntry.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapEntry
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapEntry.description: The host name to mac address table entry indexed by wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapIndex.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapIndex.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapIndex
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapIndex.description: This represents the unique index in the table.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapBridgeName.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapBridgeName
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapBridgeName.description: This represents the host name of the provider edge device. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr.description: This represents the mac address of the provider edge device. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapUseCount.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapUseCount
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapUseCount.description: This object specifies the total number of encap tunnels using this entry.

wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus.name: wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus
wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry in the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDTable.name: wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDTable
wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the BVID vlans reserved for provider backbone bridge tunnels.

wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDEntry.name: wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDEntry
wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDEntry.description: The entry to reserve BVID vlans vlans for provider backbone bridge tunnels.

wwpLeosPbtReservedBVID.name: wwpLeosPbtReservedBVID
wwpLeosPbtReservedBVID.description: This object is used to specify the VLAN ID to be reserved for PBT tunnels.

wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDRowStatus.name: wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDRowStatus
wwpLeosPbtReservedBVIDRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createandgo' will reserve the BVID VLAN for provider backbone bridge tunnels. Setting this object to 'destroy will no longer have BVID VLAN reserved for the virtual switch.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTable.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTable
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the virtual circuit mac in mac table. To create entry use SNMP multiple set operation because following mib objects needs to be set when creating entry in the table. - wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitName must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIngressISID must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEgressISID must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRowStatus must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIngressISID & wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEgressISID must be the same values.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEntry.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEntry
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEntry.description: The virtual circuit table entry index by wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIndex.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIndex.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIndex
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIndex.description: This represents the virtual circuit mac in mac index in the table. This number should be unique in the table.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitName.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitName
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitName.description: This represents the name of the mac in mac virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitFixedEncapTunnel.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitFixedEncapTunnelId
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitFixedEncapTunnel.description: This represents the fixed tunnel this virtual circuit should be mapped to.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitDestBridgeIndex.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitDestBridgeIndex
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitDestBridgeIndex.description: This represents the provider destination host name used for this tunnel. This must be set to one of the value specified by wwpLeosPbtBridgeNameMacMapIndex. if set to 0, device will interpret it as not specified.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIngressISID.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIngressISID
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitIngressISID.description: This represents the ingress ISID associated with the virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEgressISID.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEgressISID
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEgressISID.description: This represents the egress ISID associated with the virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitOperState.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitOperState
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitOperState.description: This represents the operational state of this virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEncapTunnelIdInU.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEncapTunnelIdInUse
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitEncapTunnelIdInU.description: This represents the tunnels ID of the active tunnel this virtual circuit is currently using. This tunnel can be primary of backup tunnel.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRowStatus.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRowStatus
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'destroy' If the entry exists, it will be displayed as 'active'.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRetainSTAG.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRetainSTAG
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRetainSTAG.description: When operating in PBT mode, writing TRUE(1) to this object forces this vc to retain the S-Tag. When FALSE(0) is written, the S-Tag will be popped on egress and push the tag on ingress.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStag.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStag
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStag.description: When operating in PBT mode, this is the value of the s-tag that will be used if retain-stag is set to TRUE. This is configurable only in native mode PBT. In non-native mode, this value defaults to the RVID and cannot be changed.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStatsTable.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStatsTable
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStatsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mpls virtual circuit stats table.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStatsEntry
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitStatsEntry.description: The mpls virtual circuit stats table entry index by wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitMplsIndex.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTxBytesHi.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTxBytesHi
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTxBytesHi.description: This represents the total number of higher 32 bits transmitted for given virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTxBytesLo.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTxBytesLo
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitTxBytesLo.description: This represents the total number of lower 32 bits transmitted for given virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRxBytesHi.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRxBytesHi
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRxBytesHi.description: This represents the total number of higher 32 bits received for given mpls virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRxBytesLo.name: wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRxBytesLo
wwpLeosPbtVirtualCircuitRxBytesLo.description: This represents the total number of lower 32 bits received for given virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapTable.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapTable
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the host names to mac mapping table. To create entry in this table use SNMP multiple set operation. - wwpLeosPbtHostNameMacMapHostName must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtHostNameMacMapMacAddr must be specified. - wwpLeosPbtHostNameMacMapRowStatus must be specified.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapEntry.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapEntry
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapEntry.description: The host name to mac address table entry indexed by wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapIndex.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapIndex.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapIndex
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapIndex.description: This represents the unique index in the table.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapBridgeNam.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapBridgeName
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapBridgeNam.description: This represents the host name of the provider edge device. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapMacAddr.description: This represents the mac address of the provider edge device. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapUseCount.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapUseCount
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapUseCount.description: This object specifies the total number of encap tunnels using this entry.

wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus.name: wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus
wwpLeosPbtLocalBridgeNameMacMapRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry in the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceTable.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceTable
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the Pbt Service table. To create entry in this table use SNMP multiple set operation. - wwpLeosTcePbtServiceName must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtServiceIngressIsId must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtServiceEgressIsId must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtServiceRowStatus must be specified.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceEntry.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceEntry
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceEntry.description: The Pbt Service table entry indexed by wwpLeosTcePbtServiceIndex.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceIndex.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceIndex.description: This represents the unique index in the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceName
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceName.description: This represents the Pbt service name. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceOperStatus.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceOperStatus
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceOperStatus.description: This represents the operational state of this service.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFloodContProfileId.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFloodContProfileId
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFloodContProfileId.description: Pbt Service Ingress Flood Container Profile Index

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFloodContProfileName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFloodContProfileName
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFloodContProfileName.description: Pbt Service Ingress Flood Container Profile Name

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceVsIndex.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceVsIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceVsIndex.description: Vs Index to which Pbt service is attached. To detach Pbt Service with the VS, set this object to 0.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceVsName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceVsName
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceVsName.description: Virtual Switch Name to which Pbt Service is attached.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFrameCosMapIndex.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFrameCosMapIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFrameCosMapIndex.description: Pbt Service Frame Cos Map Index

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFrameCosMapName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFrameCosMapName
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceFrameCosMapName.description: Pbt Service Frame Cos Map Name

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceResolvedCosProfileIn.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceResolvedCosProfileIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceResolvedCosProfileIn.description: Pbt Service Resolved Cos Profile Index

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceResolvedCosProfileNa.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceResolvedCosProfileName
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceResolvedCosProfileNa.description: Pbt Service Resolved Cos Profile Name

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceRowStatus.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceRowStatus
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry in the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupTable.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupTable
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the Pbt tunnel group table. To create entry in this table use SNMP multiple set operation. - wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupName must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupRowStatus must be specified.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupEntry.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupEntry
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupEntry.description: This represents an entry of the Pbt tunnel group table.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupIndex.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupIndex.description: This represents the unique index in the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupName
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupName.description: This represents the tunnel group name. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupOperStatus.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupOperStatus
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupOperStatus.description: This represents the operational state of this service.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupActivePair.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupActivePair
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupActivePair.description: An active PBT tunnel pair is two bidirectional tunnels, one inbound and the other outbound, between the same pair of devices paired together to represent a bidirectional PBT trunk. An inbound and an outbound tunnel must map to the same physical port of the device to qualify for the pairing.

wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupRowStatus.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupRowStatus
wwpLeosTcePbtTnlGroupRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry in the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlTable.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlTable
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the PBT encap tunnels. To create entry in this table use SNMP multiple set operation. - wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlName must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlRemoteBridgeIndex must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlBvId must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlPgId must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlRowStatus must be specified.

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlIndex.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlIndex.description: This represents the unique index in the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlName
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlName.description: This represents the encap tunnel name. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlFaults.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlFaults
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlFaults.description: Each Bit Represents a fault. Value 0 represents no fault. First LSB represents port Fault. Second LSB represents CFM fault and third LSB represent Admin Fault.

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlReversionToPairInde.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlReversionToPairIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlReversionToPairInde.description: Reversion occurs to this tunnel pair index in a tunnel group and is used in the definition of trap..

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlReversionFromPairIn.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlReversionFromPairIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlReversionFromPairIn.description: Reversion occurs from this tunnel pair index in a tunnel group and is used in the definition of trap.

wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlRowStatus.name: wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlRowStatus
wwpLeosTcePbtEncapTnlRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry in the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlTable.name: wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlTable
wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the PBT decap tunnels. To create entry in this table use SNMP multiple set operation. - wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlName must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlBvId must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlPgId must be specified. - wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlRowStatus must be specified.

wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlIndex.name: wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlIndex.description: This represents the unique index in the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlName.name: wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlName
wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlName.description: This represents the decap tunnel name. This object is not allowed to be modified.

wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlFaults.name: wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlFaults
wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlFaults.description: Each Bit Represents a fault. Value 0 represents no fault. First LSB represents port Fault. Second LSB represents CFM fault and value 3 represents port and CFM fault.

wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlRowStatus.name: wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlRowStatus
wwpLeosTcePbtDecapTnlRowStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry in the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformTable
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: Table of pbt service user frame L2 Transform table. Two entries in this table are automatically created when a pbt service is created (one for ingress and one for egress). The entries are deleted from this table when the corresponding pbt service is deleted. Therefore, there is no rowStatus field exposed in this mib-table entry.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformEntry
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: Logical Interface entry in the Logical Interfaces Table.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformDirection
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies pbt service L2 Transform direction of either ingress or egress.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformTagIndex
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies pbt service user frame L2 Transform direction entry index. Initial deployment supports a single tag transform. As such, tag index 2 will always have tag action of none(1).

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformTagAction
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies pbt service L2 Transform Action Type. Initial deployment supports egress/encap actions including none(1) and push(2). Initial deployment supports ingress/decap actions including none(1) and pop(3).

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformTagValue
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies pbt service L2 Transform tag value.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformTagEtype
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies the L2 transform Etype. The Etype must be specified for a push action. The Etype MAY be specified for a stamp action.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformTagPriority
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies the L2 transform tag static or fixed priority. Use of this value depends on the L2 transform action, e.g., push or stamp, as well as the priority policy.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformPriPolicy
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies L2 Transform for the L2 tag priority.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformUseTagValue
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies to use the tag value when stamping. If the action is to push, the tag value will always be used.

wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.name: wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2TransformUseTagEtype
wwpLeosTcePbtServiceUserFrameL2Transform.description: This object specifies to use the tag etype when stamping. If the action is to push, the tag etype will always be used.

wwpLeosPbtTunnelFaultNotification.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelFaultNotification
wwpLeosPbtTunnelFaultNotification.description: This notification is sent every time the tunnel becomes operationally down.

wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionNotification.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionNotification
wwpLeosPbtTunnelReversionNotification.description: This notification is sent every time backup tunnel reverts back to primary tunnel, once primary tunnel comes up. Var binding wwpLeosVplsEncapTunnelId represents the primary tunnel ID.

wwpLeosPbtTunnelActivateNotification.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelActivateNotification
wwpLeosPbtTunnelActivateNotification.description: This notification is sent every time tunnel is activated. Var binding wwpLeosVplsEncapTunnelId represents the tunnel ID.

wwpLeosPbtTunnelDeactivateNotification.name: wwpLeosPbtTunnelDeactivateNotification
wwpLeosPbtTunnelDeactivateNotification.description: This notification is sent every time tunnel is de-activated. Var binding wwpLeosVplsEncapTunnelId represents the tunnel ID.

wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelActivateNotification.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelActivateNotification
wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelActivateNotification.description: This notification is sent everytime tunnel of the given tunnel group is activated.

wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelDeactivateNotificatio.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelDeactivateNotification
wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelDeactivateNotificatio.description: This notification is sent everytime tunnel of the given tunnel group is deactivated.

wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelReversionNotification.name: wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelReversionNotification
wwpLeosTcePbtTunnelReversionNotification.description: Upon the failure of the primary tunnel, traffic is moved over to the backup tunnel at the tunnel ingress. Tunnel reversion signifies the restoration of traffic from this backup tunnel (now active) to the primary (now standby) after the primary tunnel is restored. This notification is generated when this reversion occurs.

pbtGlobalConfigGroup.name: pbtGlobalConfigGroup
pbtGlobalConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable global PBT confoguration.

pbtBridgeNameMacMapGroup.name: pbtBridgeNameMacMapGroup
pbtBridgeNameMacMapGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable to BridgeName to mac mapping.

pbtReserveBvidGroup.name: pbtReserveBvidGroup
pbtReserveBvidGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable to BVID reservation.

pbtVirtualCircuitGroup.name: pbtVirtualCircuitGroup
pbtVirtualCircuitGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable to PBT virtual circuit configuration.

pbtVirtualCircuitStatsGroup.name: pbtVirtualCircuitStatsGroup
pbtVirtualCircuitStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable to virtual circuit stats group.
